1) to offer Mexico good water (as low as 1120 ppm., with the agreement of the
                    Basin states) immediately with some decline in quality over the term of the
                    agreement (presumably five years);

1) revert to the salinity figures in the September 1971 proposal (which were
                    extremely close to our own of November) with provision for declining salinity,
                    however gradual;
